    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require payslips to state the holiday gained and remaining",
        "additional_details": "In this link, you will find the guardian explain that staff working for agencies are earning an average of 22p an hour less than employees for exactly the same work.\r\n\r\nhttps://www.theguardian.com/business/2018/nov/30/uk-agency-workers-lose-out-on-500m-a-year-in-missing-holiday-pay \r\n\r\nThe government page offers a way to calculate holiday entitlement but this system is not fair, as main employees and in some occasions, employers, are losing money with it.\r\n\r\nhttps://www.gov.uk/calculate-your-holiday-entitlement",
        "background": "It has been said in the Guardian that UK agency workers lose out on \u00a3500m a year in missing holiday pay, but this amount is greater, as it does not include the miscalculations on employees working irregular or in zero hour contracts.",
